Project Report Reflection
What surprised me most during this research was the psychological engineering behind UPI scams. I initially thought cybercrime was mostly about complex hacking or coding, but I realized that scammers primarily exploit "urgency" and "distraction." The fact that someone can be tricked into "paying" for an item they are supposed to be "selling" simply by misusing a QR code is a sobering reminder of how easily our brains can be bypassed during a transaction.
As a result, the habit I will personally change is my approach to App Permissions. I used to blindly "Allow All" when installing new tools for my projects or editing. Moving forward, I will conduct a monthly "Permission Audit" on my devices, specifically revoking SMS and Microphone access for any app that doesn't strictly require it to function.

